wikipedia_page.main: Charles Carew Page (25 April 1884 – 10 April 1921) was an English amateur cricketer who played first-class cricket for Middlesex and Cambridge University from 1905 to 1909. He was born in Barnet and died in Woking.A "free and stylish batsman", Page's highest score was 164 not out for Middlesex against Somerset at Lord's in 1908, made out of 262 in 110 minutes, and including 28 fours. His other century was 117 for Middlesex against Lancashire, also at Lord's, in 1905.Page was also a football player for Cambridge, Old Malvernians and the Corinthians.
